rom this perspective, this volume intends to reflect and promote deeper interaction and collaboration between philosophers and logicians investigating the concept of truth than has existed so far.Aside from an extended introductory overview of recent work in the theory of truth, the volume consists of articles by leading philosophers and logicians on subjects and debates that are situated on the interface between logical and philosophical theories of truth. The volume is intended for graduate students in philosophy and in logic who want an introduction to contemporary research in this area, as well as for professional philosophers and logicians  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLogic, Symbolic and mathematical. 0aTruth. 4aAufsatzsammlung. 4aMathematische Logik. 4aWahrheitstheorie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh1 aBurgess, John P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCantini, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalbach, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalbach, Volker, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHorsten, Leon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorsten, Leon, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHorwich, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeitgeb, Hannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGee, Vann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShapiro, Stewart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSheard, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 